# Code Style

## Components

- TypeScript functional components with hooks
- `"use client"` when using hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs
- Single responsibility; extract reusable logic to custom hooks
- JSDoc for complex APIs (`@param`, `@returns`, usage examples)
- Export helpers before the main component
- Animation configs in co-located `animationConfig.ts`
- Use `forwardRef` when exposing refs for focus management

## Styling

- Tailwind for layout/spacing; custom utility classes from `globals.css` for colors/buttons
- Avoid inline styles unless necessary

## File organization

| What | Where |
|------|-------|
| Components | `src/app/components/{common,contact,hero,layout,sections}/` |
| Pages | `src/app/(pages)/[route]/` |
| Data | `src/app/data/` |
| Types | `src/types/` |
| Utils | `src/utils/` |
| Styles | `src/app/globals.css` |
| Unit tests | `test/unit/` (mirrors `src/`) |
| E2E tests | `test/e2e/` |

Use barrel exports (`index.ts`) in every folder.

## Imports

Always use `@/` absolute imports. Prefer barrel exports.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { services } from "@/app/data"
import { NavLink } from "@/types"

// ❌ BAD
import { services } from "../../data/services"
```

Exception: Next.js core imports (`next/link`, `next/image`).

## Naming

- Components: PascalCase (`HeroSection.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (`formatDate`)
- CSS classes: kebab-case for custom, Tailwind as-is
- Barrel files: always `index.ts`
